  <h1>
   is_numeric
  </h1>
  This function returns whether a given variable is a numeric value (real, int32, int64 or boolean) or not. In some cases you want to check and see if a variable in
  <span>
   GameMaker
  </span>
  holds any numeric value, and that's when you would use this function. The function will return
  <span>
   true
  </span>
  if the given input is numeric, and
  <span>
   false
  </span>
  otherwise.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">is_numeric(n);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      n
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm#variable">
        Variable
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The input to check.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Boolean
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   <b>
    Example:
   </b>
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if is_numeric(val)
{
    current_val += val;
}
</code></pre>
  The above code checks the variable "val" to see if it is a numeric value and if it is it then adds it to the given variable.
 </body>
